OCI Falls As Much As 6.3% After JPMorgan Cuts Stock Rating

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-09-06T00:15:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/oci-falls-as-much-as-6-3-after-jpmorgan-cuts-stock-rating.html
OCI Co. tumbled as much as 6.3
percent in Seoul trading after JPMorgan Chase & Co. cut its
stock rating to “neutral,” citing a lack of earnings momentum.
 South Korea ’s biggest maker of polysilicon fell to 267,000 won
as of 9:15 a.m. on the Korea Exchange. The benchmark Kospi Index
dropped 1.5 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in Seoul at 
